  <info>
    <title>Applying multiple changes at once</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
  </info>

  <para>
    &sleha; provides different ways to apply multiple cluster changes simultaneously. This is
    sometimes necessary when you make changes that are dependent on each other. For example,
    a group of related resources might need to have colocation or order constraints in place
    before the resources start.
  </para>
  <para>
    You can use one of the following methods to make batch changes:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <xref linkend="ha-crmsh-changing-configuration-with-interactive-mode"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <xref linkend="ha-hawk-changing-configuration-with-batch-mode"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <xref linkend="ha-loading-configuration-changes-from-file"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
